WEBVTT

00:00.127 --> 00:03.463
[Bells jingling, bird cries]

00:05.382 --> 00:07.865
[Clears throat]

00:07.867 --> 00:10.067
♪ The plot is gaining steam ♪

00:10.069 --> 00:12.037
♪ So back to this old theme ♪

00:12.038 --> 00:15.773
♪ Here's what's been happening
on "Galavant" ♪

00:20.079 --> 00:21.613
♪ When we saw Izzy last ♪

00:21.614 --> 00:22.881
♪ This guy had been outcast ♪

00:22.882 --> 00:26.017
♪ He vowed revenge and fled to Madalena ♪

00:26.018 --> 00:27.118
♪ He brought to her palais ♪

00:27.119 --> 00:28.853
♪ The dark, dark evil way... ♪

00:28.854 --> 00:31.523
♪ Gareth's against it,
but the queen's insaner ♪

00:31.524 --> 00:34.025
♪ Will she use it and go overboard? ♪

00:34.026 --> 00:37.762
♪ Not if the man who wields
this sword stands tall ♪

00:37.763 --> 00:40.532
♪ The hero that they call
the one true king of all ♪

00:40.533 --> 00:43.001
♪ Which brings us back to Galavant ♪

00:43.002 --> 00:46.071
♪ And our hero plows ahead,
his army's kinda dead ♪

00:46.072 --> 00:48.540
♪ And yet, his energy
is far from flaggin' ♪

00:48.541 --> 00:50.609
♪ King Richard rides with Gal ♪

00:50.610 --> 00:52.110
♪ Bringing his lizard pal ♪

00:52.111 --> 00:54.512
♪ Which may or may not be
a real, live dragon ♪

00:54.513 --> 00:56.014
♪ Plus, he's got the sword ♪

00:56.015 --> 00:57.749
♪ Which you'll recall means ♪

00:57.750 --> 01:00.085
♪ He's the king who'll rule them all ♪

01:00.086 --> 01:01.152
And so!

01:01.153 --> 01:02.420
♪ To war three armies go ♪

01:02.421 --> 01:03.922
♪ One evil, one so-so ♪

01:03.923 --> 01:08.592
♪ One dead and led by Galava-a-a-nt ♪

01:09.328 --> 01:14.933
♪ Will Richard kill
his former best friend ♪

01:14.934 --> 01:20.639
♪ Who stole queen and crown
and made him look buffoony? ♪

01:20.640 --> 01:26.144
♪ Can Gal still win back
the princess again? ♪

01:26.145 --> 01:28.847
True... they're more than likely through.

01:28.848 --> 01:33.317
♪ Unless he can re-do that
really awful smooch-a-roony ♪

01:33.953 --> 01:35.553
♪ And Sid is who-knows-where ♪

01:35.554 --> 01:37.188
♪ Him and his awesome hair ♪

01:37.189 --> 01:39.924
♪ Seeking redemption for a little while ♪

01:39.925 --> 01:41.192
♪ And Roberta's said goodbye ♪

01:41.193 --> 01:43.061
♪ Since Richard's sure to die ♪

01:43.062 --> 01:45.764
♪ And now she's on her way
to Spinster Island ♪

01:45.765 --> 01:48.500
♪ Gosh, so much to dump upon your doormat ♪

01:48.501 --> 01:51.503
♪ In our half-hour sitcom format ♪

01:51.504 --> 01:53.271
♪ Still, there's plot holes we must fill ♪

01:53.272 --> 01:54.939
♪ And though I doubt we will ♪

01:54.940 --> 02:04.015
♪ We're gonna try on "Galava-a-a-a-a-nt" ♪

02:04.016 --> 02:06.016
[Bell jingles]

02:07.787 --> 02:09.454
[Horse snorts]

02:09.455 --> 02:12.657
[Wind blowing]

02:12.658 --> 02:15.860
[Applause]

02:15.861 --> 02:17.162
Oh, thank you.

02:17.163 --> 02:18.396
[Cheers and applause]

02:18.397 --> 02:20.699
Oh, thank you. Thank you very much.

02:20.700 --> 02:23.836
Here all week... Unless I die.
Thank you. Thank you very much.

02:23.836 --> 02:27.339
I got to admit... The boy can sing.

02:27.340 --> 02:30.542
Galavant - S02E09
Battle of the Three Armies

02:30.543 --> 02:31.543
[applause continues]

02:31.544 --> 02:32.744
Okay, cut it.

02:32.745 --> 02:34.346
The recap song's over.

02:34.347 --> 02:35.714
It's time for war!

02:35.715 --> 02:37.048
- Yeah! Yeah!
- Yeah! Yeah!

02:37.049 --> 02:40.585
Yes. War indeed.

02:40.586 --> 02:43.388
Shall we retire to the royal viewing area?

02:43.389 --> 02:45.557
It's up the hill a pace,
safe from the fighting.

02:45.558 --> 02:46.658
And they've got cookies.

02:46.659 --> 02:48.593
Oh! Yes, please. [Laughs]

02:48.594 --> 02:51.162
Hold on a minute. What...
What do you mean, viewing area?

02:51.163 --> 02:52.664
I thought we were gonna fight!

02:52.665 --> 02:55.300
I know, but Mr. Wormwood
had that cool skybox made,

02:55.301 --> 02:57.802
and we are king and queen,
which means technically we should...

02:57.803 --> 02:59.693
Your eyes are doing that thing again.

03:00.906 --> 03:02.741
- What? Don't be crazy. No, they're not.
- I didn't see anything. Did you?

03:02.742 --> 03:03.908
[Horse grunts]

03:03.909 --> 03:05.542
Let's go.

03:07.513 --> 03:08.813
Wow.

03:08.814 --> 03:10.215
There's a lot of them.

03:10.216 --> 03:13.685
Yeah, as a former king
who once led armies into battle,

03:13.686 --> 03:15.587
I must officially say

03:15.588 --> 03:17.956
we are knee-deep in poopie-ka-ka.

03:17.957 --> 03:19.257
Thanks, dad. That's helpful.

03:19.258 --> 03:20.692
No problem.

03:20.693 --> 03:22.093
Actually, I think I've come up with a plan

03:22.094 --> 03:23.595
that could turn this whole thing
in our favor.

03:23.596 --> 03:25.263
Well, tell me what it is, Jester.

03:25.264 --> 03:26.865
We beat them to the punch.

03:26.866 --> 03:29.134
We kill ourselves before they kill us.

03:29.135 --> 03:31.236
It's sure to ruin their morale.

03:31.237 --> 03:34.739
If only I were alive
to see the looks on their faces.

03:34.740 --> 03:36.241
[Army murmuring]

03:36.242 --> 03:37.542
[Clicks tongue]

03:37.543 --> 03:40.412
Good people of Hortensia,

03:40.413 --> 03:43.815
it is true the Valencians
have three to our every one.

03:43.816 --> 03:46.084
And you are right to worry

03:46.085 --> 03:48.219
because how can so few of us

03:48.220 --> 03:50.588
dig the graves of so many of them?!

03:50.589 --> 03:52.557
[Army cheering]

03:52.558 --> 03:54.459
She twisted it.

03:54.460 --> 03:57.695
If you want to leave, leave now.

03:57.696 --> 03:59.564
I will not mind,

03:59.565 --> 04:04.169
for it will leave more glory
for the rest of us!

04:04.170 --> 04:05.737
[Army cheering]

04:05.738 --> 04:07.472
She twisted it again!

04:07.473 --> 04:09.941
Arise, Hortensia!

04:09.942 --> 04:12.610
Today, we fight!

04:12.611 --> 04:16.714
Pots shall be broken,
pans shall be splintered!

04:16.714 --> 04:17.949
Whisks shall be...

04:17.950 --> 04:20.652
Actually, let's not use whisks.

04:20.653 --> 04:24.055
It'll be a sore day, a red day,

04:24.056 --> 04:26.791
but a day for victory!

04:26.792 --> 04:28.126
[Army cheering]

04:28.127 --> 04:30.261
Victory!

04:30.262 --> 04:33.198
Stand strong! Stand strong!

04:33.199 --> 04:36.501
Stand strong and fight!

04:36.502 --> 04:37.868
[Sword clacking]

04:41.340 --> 04:43.341
Oy.

04:43.342 --> 04:45.576
We are completely screwed.

04:49.715 --> 04:52.449
[Heroic music plays]

04:56.776 --> 04:57.977
[Inhales deeply]

04:57.978 --> 05:00.546
Oh, I haven't been in a proper
battle in a long time.

05:00.547 --> 05:04.448
I'm gonna ride up just at the perfect moment
in front of Isabella and save the day.

05:04.450 --> 05:05.484
Mwah!

05:05.485 --> 05:06.852
Yeah.

05:06.853 --> 05:09.588
This is gonna be super fun.

05:09.589 --> 05:11.823
[Laughs] You're gonna be fine.

05:11.824 --> 05:13.859
[Chuckling] Oh, totally.

05:13.860 --> 05:14.860
I know.

05:14.861 --> 05:16.928
I'm feeling great and confident.

05:16.929 --> 05:18.897
I-I'm just worried about Tad Cooper.

05:18.898 --> 05:21.066
I mean, the little fellow is terrified.

05:21.067 --> 05:23.078
Just look at him.

05:23.070 --> 05:25.838
Richard, you can do this.

05:25.839 --> 05:27.740
Over the last months,
I've watched you transform

05:27.741 --> 05:30.409
from a boob into a real man.

05:30.410 --> 05:32.578
And today, you're gonna
transform into a warrior.

05:32.579 --> 05:33.879
You said "boob."

05:33.880 --> 05:35.881
Please focus.

05:35.882 --> 05:38.350
Sorry.

05:38.351 --> 05:39.918
All right, my friend.

05:39.919 --> 05:41.220
If ever there was a moment

05:41.221 --> 05:43.689
for you to become
the dragon that I know you are,

05:43.690 --> 05:45.791
this is it.

05:45.792 --> 05:47.759
Breathe fire!

05:50.296 --> 05:52.096
Okay, I'll check in with you later.

05:54.467 --> 05:56.335
Oh, why do we need these?

05:56.336 --> 05:57.870
Are we not doing our own stunts?

05:57.871 --> 05:59.505
What? Of course we are.

05:59.506 --> 06:01.206
Just to preserve the dramatic reveal.

06:01.207 --> 06:03.742
Ah. That's a good idea.

06:03.743 --> 06:05.811
You've obviously done this before.

06:05.812 --> 06:07.812
♪

06:09.616 --> 06:12.251
Okay, are we gonna start this war or not?

06:12.252 --> 06:13.418
I say we wait.

06:13.419 --> 06:16.288
In an hour, the sun
will be at the perfect angle

06:16.289 --> 06:18.524
to highlight the color
of the spilling blood

06:18.525 --> 06:20.125
against the golden sand.

06:20.126 --> 06:22.994
It'll be spectacular for the royal painter.

06:24.564 --> 06:26.231
Brilliant. Then we wait.

06:26.232 --> 06:27.766
Okay. What's going on here?

06:27.767 --> 06:30.736
- Hmm?
- This war was my birthday present.

06:30.737 --> 06:34.072
It was supposed to be me and you
down there killing people,

06:34.073 --> 06:37.142
not sitting in some luxury box
eating humongous raisins.

06:37.143 --> 06:39.678
[Scoffs] Actually, I-it's figs.

06:39.679 --> 06:41.680
I feel something's changed.

06:41.681 --> 06:43.549
Nothing's changed, Gareth.

06:43.550 --> 06:46.351
Well, then, let's go down there,
hack up a few folk,

06:46.352 --> 06:48.986
and go on our vacation
just like we talked about.

06:50.456 --> 06:52.324
Yeah, um, about that.

06:52.325 --> 06:55.027
Look, Gareth, um...

06:55.027 --> 06:56.527
Let's put off the vacation.

06:56.529 --> 06:57.562
- Just for a bit.
- [Sighs]

06:57.564 --> 07:00.732
I mean, we would have
just conquered a new kingdom,

07:00.733 --> 07:02.534
and it would be impolite

07:02.535 --> 07:03.936
to leave Mr. Wormwood all by himself

07:03.937 --> 07:06.939
after he was kind enough
to bring us this conflict.

07:06.940 --> 07:09.942
Has this got something to do
with that dew-dew dark magic stuff?

07:09.943 --> 07:11.743
Actually, it's D'Dew.

07:11.744 --> 07:14.012
Two darks... Dark-dark evil way.

07:14.013 --> 07:15.948
- Back off!
- Of course not, Gareth.

07:15.949 --> 07:16.914
I swear.

07:18.284 --> 07:20.752
Hold the crow.

07:20.753 --> 07:22.554
A second army approaches.

07:22.555 --> 07:26.391
Yes, being led by some
devilishly handsome hero type.

07:26.392 --> 07:29.094
Let me see that.

07:29.095 --> 07:32.097
Oh, God. It's Galavant!

07:32.098 --> 07:35.400
With a weirdly large beard.

07:35.401 --> 07:36.468
Right, that's it.

07:36.469 --> 07:38.003
I'm gonna go down there and cause havoc

07:38.004 --> 07:40.004
just like we planned.

07:41.875 --> 07:43.207
I hope you're gonna join me.

07:47.847 --> 07:49.047
Right.

07:49.048 --> 07:52.184
[Dramatic music plays]

07:52.185 --> 07:54.119
Okay, you dogs!

07:54.120 --> 07:56.521
To battle!

07:56.522 --> 07:58.857
[Army cheering]

07:58.858 --> 08:00.758
♪

08:02.762 --> 08:05.364
♪ It's a good day to die ♪

08:05.365 --> 08:07.666
♪ To stand and fight until we're dead ♪

08:07.667 --> 08:09.968
♪ A good day to die ♪

08:09.969 --> 08:14.106
♪ Though if somebody
ever said, "for what?" ♪

08:14.107 --> 08:17.042
♪ We forgot ♪

08:17.043 --> 08:20.645
♪ So on reflection, perhaps maybe not ♪

08:23.850 --> 08:25.017
Who is that?

08:25.018 --> 08:27.319
Looks like they're advancing
on the Valencians.

08:27.320 --> 08:29.755
I can't tell, but they missed my song.

08:29.756 --> 08:31.957
Maybe we ask them to wait
so I can run out and sing it again.

08:31.958 --> 08:33.625
Oh, we'll run out there, Jester.

08:33.626 --> 08:34.625
But to fight.

08:35.761 --> 08:38.931
Hortensians, this is our chance!

08:38.932 --> 08:40.164
Yeah, let's do this.

08:40.166 --> 08:42.700
I'm just gonna go and check
things are locked up.

08:44.771 --> 08:46.071
Move out!

08:46.072 --> 08:48.072
[Army cheering]

08:49.542 --> 08:52.044
♪ It's a good day to die ♪

08:52.045 --> 08:54.746
♪ Though not as good as other days ♪

08:54.747 --> 08:56.782
♪ A good day to die ♪

08:56.783 --> 09:00.686
♪ But if there's one a little ways away ♪

09:00.687 --> 09:03.789
♪ Well, then, hey ♪

09:03.790 --> 09:05.324
♪ We can reschedule ♪

09:05.325 --> 09:08.559
♪ It's more than okay ♪

09:11.564 --> 09:13.532
Another beautiful day in the country.

09:13.533 --> 09:15.334
Here's some potatoes for you, bae.

09:15.335 --> 09:17.970
These have bugs. Yay! Extra protein.

09:17.971 --> 09:19.972
[Footsteps approaching]

09:19.973 --> 09:22.106
♪

09:24.577 --> 09:29.715
♪ This is a day,
just a day like every other ♪

09:29.716 --> 09:31.149
Is everything okay?

09:31.150 --> 09:34.052
[Army shouting]

09:34.053 --> 09:37.855
♪ We've lived as best we could ♪

09:39.058 --> 09:41.959
Looks like we have guests.

09:43.629 --> 09:48.834
♪ And I must say,
though we may not get another ♪

09:48.835 --> 09:50.668
[Shouting continues]

09:53.639 --> 09:55.674
♪ If I'm with you ♪

09:55.675 --> 09:59.211
♪ Then our last will at least be good ♪

09:59.212 --> 10:02.346
Well, at least we made it to 25.

10:07.653 --> 10:09.821
♪ It's a good day to die ♪

10:09.822 --> 10:12.657
♪ To spurt our blood and spill our guts ♪

10:12.658 --> 10:14.559
♪ A good day to die ♪

10:14.560 --> 10:17.295
- ♪ Good day to die ♪
- ♪ Out loud, it sounds completely nuts ♪

10:17.296 --> 10:19.431
♪ But still ♪

10:19.432 --> 10:21.633
- ♪ Blood will spill ♪
- [Whistling]

10:21.634 --> 10:26.271
♪ After that, it will all go downhill ♪

10:26.272 --> 10:28.039
She doesn't want to go on vacation!

10:29.976 --> 10:31.777
We were supposed to go zip-lining.

10:31.778 --> 10:33.345
Who doesn't like zip-lining?

10:33.346 --> 10:34.145
Huh?

10:35.348 --> 10:39.518
♪ We will try not to die, but we will ♪

10:39.519 --> 10:41.086
Aah! [Grunts]

10:41.087 --> 10:42.821
To victory!

10:42.822 --> 10:47.959
♪ In the meantime, I guess we can kill ♪

10:47.960 --> 10:49.694
Richard, have you seen Isabella?

10:49.695 --> 10:52.364
- Aah! Aah!
- ♪ And we'll fight, who knows why ♪

10:52.365 --> 10:54.833
♪ Till we say with a sigh ♪

10:54.834 --> 10:57.869
♪ It's a go-o-o-o-o-od ♪

10:57.870 --> 11:00.138
♪ Day to ♪

11:00.139 --> 11:03.909
♪ Di-i-i-i-i-i-e ♪

11:03.910 --> 11:05.976
Time out! Can we call a time out?!

11:07.503 --> 11:10.136
[Weapons clanking]

11:10.138 --> 11:12.171
[Armies shouting]

11:13.111 --> 11:14.712
Isn't this amazing?

11:14.713 --> 11:17.148
We sit here while they do
our dirty work for us.

11:17.149 --> 11:19.383
Isn't it crazy what you can talk
people into doing?

11:19.384 --> 11:21.552
Well, I thank God
for the class system every day.

11:21.553 --> 11:23.020
Mm-hmm. Me too.

11:23.021 --> 11:24.188
[Sighs]

11:24.189 --> 11:25.689
Oh, no.

11:27.326 --> 11:29.426
This isn't good.

11:30.329 --> 11:31.629
Ohh.

11:31.630 --> 11:33.998
The sword of the one true king.

11:33.999 --> 11:36.934
And he's down there.

11:36.935 --> 11:38.436
And he's a god.

11:38.437 --> 11:40.705
This is madness!

11:40.706 --> 11:41.839
Aah! Aah!

11:41.840 --> 11:44.375
Mm. Isabella wasn't lying.

11:44.376 --> 11:46.310
He's on their side.

11:46.311 --> 11:48.913
It's time... for D'Dew.

11:48.914 --> 11:50.781
Actually, I've been having second thoughts

11:50.782 --> 11:52.717
- about the dark, evil way.
- Two darks... dark-dark.

11:52.718 --> 11:55.052
Why is it so hard for people to remember?

11:55.053 --> 11:57.421
It's just I care about Gareth,
and I promised I wouldn't use it.

11:57.422 --> 12:01.559
And he seemed super upset
about the vacation.

12:01.560 --> 12:03.561
Maybe I'll... I'll go down
and help him fight.

12:03.562 --> 12:06.330
Look. May I be blunt?

12:06.331 --> 12:08.332
You want power. I offer it.

12:08.333 --> 12:11.936
You want control.
It's yours for the taking.

12:11.937 --> 12:14.905
You want the whole enchilada.

12:14.906 --> 12:16.806
It's magic hour, baby.

12:18.201 --> 12:19.977
May I be even blunter?

12:19.978 --> 12:22.213
Screw Gareth. He's weak.

12:22.214 --> 12:24.481
Losers vacation. Closers use magic.

12:26.284 --> 12:28.618
Shall we finish this thing?

12:30.789 --> 12:32.056
Should have stayed with Roberta.

12:32.057 --> 12:33.758
Why do I always have to be so damn heroic?

12:33.759 --> 12:35.459
You've got a lifetime to be with Roberta!

12:35.460 --> 12:36.993
You've got one day to be immortal.

12:38.897 --> 12:40.665
Today, you can be...

12:40.666 --> 12:41.866
Aah!

12:41.867 --> 12:43.000
Isabella!

12:43.001 --> 12:44.567
I don't want to be Isabella!
I want to be me!

12:45.737 --> 12:47.103
Where the hell are you going?!

12:51.243 --> 12:53.678
That's one hell of a sword.

12:53.679 --> 12:55.179
Aah! Yah!

12:55.180 --> 12:56.613
Isabella.

12:57.616 --> 12:58.883
I've come for you.

12:58.884 --> 13:00.084
Galavant?

13:00.085 --> 13:01.651
My love.

13:07.159 --> 13:08.693
Gareth?

13:08.694 --> 13:09.726
Richard?

13:11.096 --> 13:13.297
Look. I know you're upset.

13:13.298 --> 13:14.565
Okay?

13:14.566 --> 13:16.467
I'll give you that one
'cause it's been upsetting.

13:16.468 --> 13:18.436
Izzy, please.
Can we just be done with this?

13:18.437 --> 13:20.137
Isabella. Look.

13:20.138 --> 13:21.872
I didn't tell you to die in a brown fart.

13:21.873 --> 13:24.542
The truth is, all I've wanted
is to come back to you.

13:24.543 --> 13:26.110
You're the love of my life.

13:26.111 --> 13:28.546
And if we survive this,
I want to marry you.

13:28.547 --> 13:30.648
And I want to live by the sea...

13:30.649 --> 13:32.449
You had me at "brown fart."

13:36.575 --> 13:38.422
Still sort of yeasty.

13:38.423 --> 13:39.690
And a little bit musty.

13:39.691 --> 13:41.858
But we've got a lifetime to work on it.

13:42.997 --> 13:45.196
I know I've got a lot
to apologize to you for.

13:45.197 --> 13:47.164
Don't be ridiculous.

13:47.165 --> 13:49.700
It's just good to see you again,
my old friend.

13:49.701 --> 13:52.836
[Horn blows]

13:56.174 --> 13:58.843
What was that?

13:58.844 --> 14:00.077
[Horn blows]

14:00.078 --> 14:01.112
Whoa!

14:01.113 --> 14:03.614
Whoa, whoa. We're on the same team.

14:03.615 --> 14:04.749
I'm with Galavant,

14:04.750 --> 14:06.050
fighting for true love and all that?

14:06.051 --> 14:09.587
Galavant, the undead army is turning on us!

14:09.588 --> 14:11.422
I know. They're doing it here, too!

14:11.423 --> 14:12.890
- You can control the dead?
- Oh, yes.

14:12.891 --> 14:14.925
Not only control, but make them stronger.

14:14.926 --> 14:16.193
Ha!

14:16.194 --> 14:20.064
Seems Galavant has brought the wrong
covered dish to the potluck dinner.

14:20.065 --> 14:21.465
Ha!

14:21.466 --> 14:24.101
They're kind of attacking
everyone, our men included.

14:24.102 --> 14:26.504
Well, you make a cake,
you break a few eggs.

14:26.505 --> 14:28.439
So, how do we do this?

14:28.440 --> 14:30.608
